{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Proteins in this entry are related to ClpA ([swissprot:P0ABH9]) from Escherichia coli. ClpA is an ATP-dependent chaperone and part of the ClpAP protease that participates in regulatory protein degradation and the dissolution and degradation of protein aggregates [[cite:PUB00020759]]. ClpA functions as the regulatory component of the ATP dependent protease complex ClpAP [[cite:PUB00088088]]. ClpA recognises sequences in specific proteins, which it then unfolds in an ATP-dependent manner and transports into the degradation chamber of the associated ClpP protease [[cite:PUB00020750], [cite:PUB00020760]]. A small adaptor-like protein, ClpS, modulates the activity of ClpA and is an important regulatory factor for this protein [[cite:PUB00020738]]. It protects ClpA from autodegradation and appears to redirect its activity away from soluble proteins and toward aggregated proteins.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"ncbifam" {"TIGR02639" "ATP-dependent Clp protease ATP-binding subunit ClpA"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "ATP-dependent Clp protease ATP-binding subunit ClpA", "short" "ClpA"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 14, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 3318, "taxa" 13126, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 13588, "sets" 0, "proteins" 13588, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 10605}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"gp" {"displayName" "Genome Properties", "description" "Genome properties is an annotation system whereby functional attributes can be assigned to a genome, based on the presence of a defined set of protein signatures within that genome.", "rank" 45, "accessions" [{"accession" "GenProp1137", "url" "https://www.ebi.ac.uk/interpro/genomeproperties/genome-property/GenProp1137"} {"accession" "GenProp0251", "url" "https